I am not sure how many times that this series has been requested, but I am sure it's over 50 times.

All three movies are here, in unrated format if they could exist that way.

They are made with h.264 (x.264r409: 2pass, RDO 7, 3CBF's, 8x8 Trans w/16ref) and matroska for the container.  Fucking 30 hours of encoding.

Optional external subtitles are embedded in each movie, which are available in: French, English, Or Spanish, depending on which film you are watching.

If you want to extract the subtitles for whatever reason, do this:


Download:

mkvtoolnix:
 &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.bunkus.org/videotools/mkvtoolnix/win32/mkvtoolnix-unicode-1.6.5.rar&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.bunkus.org/videotools/mkvtoolnix/win32/mkvtoolnix-unicode-1.6.5.rar&lt;/a&gt;

Unrar, and then download this:

MkvExtractGUI:
 &lt;a href=&quot;
http://corecodec.org/frs/?group_id=55&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://corecodec.org/frs/?group_id=55&lt;/a&gt;

And unrar into the same directory as &quot;mkvtoolnix&quot;.

Click on MKvExtractGUI, then when it runs, simply drag the .mkv onto the screen of MKVextractGUI.  Wait for info to be displayed on the screen.  Choose your output folder by clicking the &quot;other path&quot; button, then click the box on the shit you want.  You can extract the audio, video, everything..it's very cool.

